new X509Certificate2(Encoding.ASCII.GetBytes(pemCertString));

that works fine. Actually, windows can figure out different formats, it can be a base64 encoded certificate without the PEM frame or the DER certificate itself, it can process whatever the passed byte array contains

on Linux it seems much more picky and the constructor that gets a byte[], only accepts a DER certificate. Now what I can do is to trim the PEM frame, base64 decode the remaining data, and pass the resulting DER certificate to the constructor.

Is there any more elegant solution than the following:

